Input audio is line level, ie 1 V RMS.
Supply voltage is 12 V.
Maximum output is about 3 V RMS.

Gain can be increased for weak signals.


Adjusting the trimpots will change the voltage between test points.


NOTICE:  You should short R7 while calibrating R6.


                pot     test points value
first bias      R2      TP3 - TP1   ~1.4 V for full amplitude.
gain            R5      TP2 - TP4   Vdd - gain*(TP3-TP1)
                                    7.8 V for full amplitude and 12 V supply.
second bias     R6      TP5 - TP1   gain*(TP3-TP1)
                                    4.2 V for full amplitude
